features.additionalInfo: Wherever you are in the world, CommBank gives you the choice and control to securely manage all of your accounts on a range of devices, the way you want.

We'll send you a term deposit renewal notice roughly a week before it matures, not only as a reminder but to also explain what you can do next. You can also opt-in to get free alerts - either an email, SMS or a notification in NetBank.
Streamline your business banking and save time with automatic data feeds from your online banking to your accounting software.
If you want to withdraw your Term Deposit before it matures you'll need to give us 31 days' notice. You may incur a prepayment adjustment and administration fee.

eligibility.additionalInfo: Customers must be aged 18+ to open a personal Term Deposit. Customers must have at least one signatory aged 18+ to open a non-personal Term Deposit.
To open a Term Deposit, you must have an Australian residential address.
Personal, Joint, Self Managed Super Fund (SMSF), Business & Trust.

fees.name: Prepayment administration fee and prepayment adjustment
fees.additionalInfo: If you need to withdraw money during the term, you may request withdrawal of all or part of your funds by giving the Bank 31 days' notice. A prepayment administration fee will apply to withdrawals before maturity.In addition to this fee, a prepayment adjustment will apply to withdrawals before maturity.
